to get a fake score upon there
because I'm a lead hacker.

00:09:06.090 --> 00:09:08.350
So why not just ban
these players?

00:09:08.350 --> 00:09:09.030
WOLFF DOBSON: You
could ban them.

00:09:09.030 --> 00:09:11.400
But then they might notice and
they might get angry and come

00:09:11.400 --> 00:09:13.180
after you again.

00:09:13.180 --> 00:09:17.170
But also, really, they're still
going to appear in their

00:09:17.170 --> 00:09:18.750
social scoreboards.

00:09:18.750 --> 00:09:21.480
And so if somebody looks and
says, yeah, he's still got the

00:09:21.480 --> 00:09:23.470
highest score, that's great,
but they may be ruining the

00:09:23.470 --> 00:09:26.490
experience for the people
in the public boards.

00:09:26.490 --> 00:09:28.300
So this allows them just to be
like, well, they're not going

00:09:28.300 --> 00:09:29.850
to appear in the
public boards.

00:09:29.850 --> 00:09:33.480
And then when they look at the
public board, they'll still

00:09:33.480 --> 00:09:34.210
see themselves.

00:09:34.210 --> 00:09:36.470
But if anybody else looks at
the public board, they will

00:09:36.470 --> 00:09:36.990
not be there.

00:09:36.990 --> 00:09:37.470
TODD KERPELMAN: All right.

00:09:37.470 --> 00:09:40.170
So that's probably something
to make sure--

00:09:40.170 --> 00:09:42.290
hiding means hide from
everybody except

00:09:42.290 --> 00:09:44.160
the cheating or the--

00:09:44.160 --> 00:09:44.770
WOLFF DOBSON: Adverse--

00:09:44.770 --> 00:09:45.620
TODD KERPELMAN: --the
hidden player.

00:09:45.620 --> 00:09:46.690
WOLFF DOBSON: The
adverse player.

00:09:46.690 --> 00:09:47.300
TODD KERPELMAN: Yes.

00:09:47.300 --> 00:09:49.690
So they wouldn't even know
that they've been hidden

00:09:49.690 --> 00:09:52.380
unless they were to get another
friend with an account

00:09:52.380 --> 00:09:53.610
to look at the leaderboards.

00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:54.450
WOLFF DOBSON: Look at
public leaderboards.

00:09:54.450 --> 00:09:55.060
TODD KERPELMAN: Public
leaderboards.

00:09:55.060 --> 00:09:56.320
WOLFF DOBSON: They will appear
in the social leaderboards.

00:09:56.320 --> 00:09:57.676
TODD KERPELMAN: And that looks
like a lot of work.

00:09:57.676 --> 00:09:58.130
WOLFF DOBSON: Yeah.

00:09:58.130 --> 00:09:59.770
TODD KERPELMAN: I suppose the
other advantage is if you hide

00:09:59.770 --> 00:10:03.460
someone that you suspect has
gotten a score through

00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:05.510
